main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a black, submarine-shaped object that remained visible for 30 minutes before submerging in water in 1955.
interesting points: The object was described as black and shaped like a submarine.
It was sighted for a duration of 30 minutes before submerging.
The witness was located 1/2 mile northwest of Cherry Point in Chuckanut Bay, North West shore.
The report was submitted in accordance with AFR 200- paragraph 7, indicating the official nature of the investigation.
The conclusion stated 'UNKNOWN', indicating that the object could not be identified.
location: Chuckanut Bay, North West shore, Washington
witnesses: civilian (Mrs. Norley and Mr. Mack Baker), S/SGT Noan R. Pederson (military supervisor)
